Cyber Security Manager Job Description

We are seeking a highly skilled Cyber Security Manager to install, configure, calibrate, operate, and maintain hardware and software of IT and OT systems.

The ideal candidate will have experience in systems administration, network administration, and control system security, as well as excellent oral and written communication skills to work with multiple stakeholders.

Key responsibilities include implementing, maintaining, and assessing cybersecurity on systems and components, as well as following procedures to coordinate activities and preserve availability and functional integrity of services.
• Bachelor of Science in Engineering, Computer Science, or Information Systems and 5+ years of prior relevant experience;
• Credentials that meet DoD Cyber Workforce requirements for specialty codes 441, 451, and 462 at the intermediate level;
• United States Citizenship;
• A security clearance adequate to obtain user and privileged user access to Navy Networks and Information Systems.
